# Copy to .env.local and adjust. TarifGuard is a thin read-only client over the
# deterministic tarifhub serving API. It never computes or stores a billing value.

# --- Deterministic backend (FastAPI serving service) ---
# Base URL of the serving API. Used SERVER-SIDE only (by the route handlers in
# app/api/* and lib/api.ts). It is never exposed to the browser.
#   local uv run uvicorn tarifhub_serving.main:app --port 8000 -> http://localhost:8000
#   in-cluster (Helm)     -> http://tarifhub-serving:8000
SERVING_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000

# --- Explain feature (record-grounded, deterministic) ---
# The explain screen is served by the deterministic serving endpoint
# GET /api/v1/explain (ADR-017): it returns frozen records verbatim plus a
# rule-generated explanation. It is NOT an LLM call, and no Bedrock/Vertex
# model is invoked for explain today. Patient identifiers never leave Swiss
# infrastructure; any optional free-text context is scrubbed by lib/deident.ts
# (see lib/deident.ts) for the audit trail only and is never forwarded.
#
# LLM_PROVIDER / LLM_REGION are reserved for a future L3 patient-facing app
# (ADR-012) and are NOT used by the current console explain path.
# LLM_PROVIDER=bedrock-eu   # reserved for future L3 (ADR-012); unused by explain
# LLM_REGION=eu-central-1   # reserved for future L3 (ADR-012); unused by explain

# Ingestion review API; unset = bundled demo queue, review decisions are NOT persisted
INGEST_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
